<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Discussion.</emphasis>
This is the most widespread but least common subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fendleriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Poa fendleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Mexico. Staminate plants are rare or absent, except in Coahuila where a staminate plant has been collected. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Poa fendleriana</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">fendleriana</emphasis>
intergrades with 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fendleriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Poa fendleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subsp. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">albescens</emphasis>
in Chihuahua and in southeast Arizona and southwest New Mexico.
</paragraph>
